An Act relative to assault and battery upon a transit worker.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Section 13D of chapter 265 of the General Laws is hereby amended by striking out the
2 first paragraph and inserting in place thereof the following paragraph:-
3 Whoever commits an assault and battery, including assault and battery by means of a
4 bodily substance, upon any public employee, including but not limited to a public transit worker,
5 when such person is engaged in the performance of their duties at the time of such assault and
6 battery, shall be punished by imprisonment for not less than 90 days nor more than 2½ years in a
7 house of correction or by a fine of not less than $500 nor more than $5,000. For the purposes of
8 this section, “bodily substance” shall mean any human secretion, discharge or emission
9 including, but not limited to, blood, saliva, mucous, semen, urine or feces.
